Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine mid red-brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Phileratos/idas. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.101a,13. Trimmed. See B. Schmaltz, Die hellenistischen Amporenstempel aus Kaunos. 62, KA141 for the rarity of this stamp.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1583)
